net.sf.mmm.search.api

Interface SearchEntry

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AttributeReadId<Long>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MutableSearchEntry, SearchHit
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMutableSearchEntry, AbstractSearchEntry, BasicSearchEntry, LuceneMutableSearchEntry, LuceneSearchEntry, SearchHitImpl

    public interface SearchEntry
extends AttributeReadId<Long>
    This interface represents an entry of the search-index. A SearchEntry represents a single content (file, web-page, etc.) and consists of fields with the according metadata. It is either used for indexing (net.sf.mmm.search.indexer.api.SearchIndexer) or retrieval.
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
    See Also:
    SearchFields, SearchHit

    • Field Detail

      • FIELD_ID

        static final String FIELD_ID
        The name of the "id" field. The UID (Unique Identifier) is a field that identifies the content uniquely.
        It is strongly suggested for the implementation but NOT strictly guaranteed that the ID remains the same if a SearchEntry is updated in the index. The ID is a Long value. End-users should never make any assumptions or interpretation of its value as this is totally implementation specific.
        See Also:
        getId(), Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_TITLE

        static final String FIELD_TITLE
        The name of the "title" field. The title should always be present.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_URI

        static final String FIELD_URI
        The name of the "uri" field. The URI (Unified Resource Identifier) identifies the original content and allows to link to it. Typically this is not an entire URL but a path relative to the URL-prefix of the according source.
        NOTE:
        This field should typically be present. Only if the content has a technical UID, the FIELD_CUSTOM_ID can be used for linking the content and the URI might NOT be set then. However it is best practice to set the URI anyways (to the URL-suffix containing the UID for linking the content).
        See Also:
        getUri(), Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_CUSTOM_ID

        static final String FIELD_CUSTOM_ID
        The name of the "cid" field. The custom Identifier (CID) is an optional field that identifies the content uniquely. Unlike the ID this is an optional custom ID given by the user of this API. It can be in any arbitrary format. While the URI of a content may change (e.g. if the content is renamed or moved) the UID has to stay untouched and identifies the content for its complete lifetime.
        See Also:
        getCustomId(), Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_TEXT

        static final String FIELD_TEXT
        The name of the "text" field. This is the default field to search on. All textual information about the content should be stored in this field.
        See Also:
        getText(), Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_KEYWORDS

        static final String FIELD_KEYWORDS
        The name of the "keywords" field. This is an optional field that may hold specific keywords (also called tags) that classify the content.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_SIZE

        static final String FIELD_SIZE
        The name of the "size" field. This is an optional field that may hold the size (also called content-length) of the content. This should be a Long value representing the size in bytes.
        See Also:
        getSize(), Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_CREATOR

        static final String FIELD_CREATOR
        The name of the "creator" field. This is an optional field that may hold the author (aka artist) of the content.
        See Also:
        getCreator(), Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_TYPE

        static final String FIELD_TYPE
        The name of the "type" field. This is an optional field that classifies the type (aka format or content-type) of the content. As values typically either mime-types or file-extensions are used (but NOT mixed).
        See Also:
        getType(), Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_LANGUAGE

        static final String FIELD_LANGUAGE
        The name of the "lang" field. This is an optional field that specifies the language of the content.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FIELD_SOURCE

        static final String FIELD_SOURCE
        The name of the "source" field. This field specifies the source of the content. It is not strictly required but should always be present in a regular setup. If it is NOT present, the field URI has to contain the complete URL to the content.
        See Also:
        getSource(), SearchSource, Constant Field Values

        Object getField(String name)
        This method is a generic accessor for fields of this entry. For the predefine fields (see FIELD_* constants like FIELD_TEXT) there are specific getter methods like getText().

      • getField

        <T> T getField(String name,
               Class<T> type)
        This method is a generic accessor for fields of this entry with a specific type.
        The type String will always work. Other types have to be compatible to the field type (or a RuntimeException will be thrown).
        Type Parameters:
        T - is the generic type expected for the requested field-value (see parameter type).
        Parameters:
        name - is the name of the requested field.
        type - is the type of the requested field.
        Returns:
        the value of the requested field or null if no field exists for the given name.
